====Return to Villa====

On December 3, 2011, Guzan made his second [[Premier League]] appearance for Villa coming on for the injured [[Shay Given]] against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]. Given had been ruled out for a month with a torn hamstring so Guzan retained his place in the first team, giving him an extended run in Aston Villa's first team.

Guzan was released by Villa at the end of his contract in June 2012.<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~2786007,00.html | publisher=Aston Villa F.C. | title=Senior trio Guzan, Heskey and Cuellar head Villa released list. | date=May 23, 2012 | accessdate=May 23, 2012 }}</ref> However, he was linked with a return to the club over the summer in a situation similar to that of fellow Aston Villa goalkeeper [[Andy Marshall]] in 2010. On July 16, 2012, Guzan was included in new manager [[Paul Lambert]]'s 25-man squad for Villa's tour of the United States and the same day, the player confirmed via [[Twitter]] that he had renewed his contract and rejoined the club.<ref name="USA Tour: Confirmed Villa party set for flight">{{cite web |url=http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~2850585,00.html |title=USA Tour: Confirmed Villa party set for flight |work=Aston Villa Football Club | publisher=AVFC |date=July 16, 2012 }}</ref><ref name="Guzan confirms return on Twitter">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/bguzan/status/224826305231851520 |title=Twitter / bguzan: Excited to be going back to villa and what the future holds! Was a relaxing break,but looking forward to seeing the boys today! |work=Brad Guzan | publisher=Twitter |date=July 16, 2012 }}</ref>

He made his return for Aston Villa against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] putting in a Man of the Match performance in a 1<U+2013>1 draw at the [[St James' Park]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Nursey |first=James |url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/brad-guzan-is-determined-to-keep-shay-1300937 |title=Brad Guzan is determined to keep Shay Given out of the Aston Villa team |publisher=Mirror.co.uk |date=September 3, 2012 |accessdate=June 13, 2013}}</ref> He kept Villa's first clean sheet of the season in a 2<U+2013>0 win against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] and performed well enough to keep his position in the starting lineup. At the end of the 2012-13 Premier League season, he was voted the Aston Villa Player of the Year thanks to his large contribution to Villa's survival.<ref>{{cite web|last=Creditor |first=Avi |url=http://sports.yahoo.com/news/guzan-named-aston-villas-player-224200990--sow.html |title=Guzan named Aston Villa's Player of the Year |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date=May 7, 2013 |accessdate=June 13, 2013}}</ref>  On July 6, 2013, Guzan was rewarded for his play and signed a four-year contract extension with the Midlands club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11677/8810435/Aston-Villa-goalkeeper-Brad-Guzan-signs-new-four-year-deal |title=Aston Villa goalkeeper Brad Guzan signs new four-year deal |publisher=Sky Sports |date=July 6, 2013 |accessdate=July 6, 2013 }}</ref>

On July 18, 2013, Guzan stated that he hoped to give Aston Villa the best years of his career and said that signing a new contract was a "no-brainer".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~3263179,00.html | publisher=Aston Villa F.C. | title=Guzan: I'm delighted to be giving Villa the best years of my career | date=July 18, 2013 | accessdate=July 18, 2013}}</ref>

On 28 September 2013, Guzan remarkably got an assist for [[Andreas Weimann]] in a 3-2 win against [[Manchester City]] in which Paul Lambert praised Guzan's distribution technique for goal kicks.

==International career==
[[File:Landon Donovan and Brad Guzan.jpg|thumb|200px|Guzan (right) with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]] at the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Since 2006, Guzan has established himself as the second-choice goalkeeper for the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]] behind [[Tim Howard]]. He made his World Cup qualifying debut in the second leg of a [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification <U+2013> CONCACAF Second Round|second round]] qualifier against [[Barbados national football team|Barbados]] (with the US up 8<U+2013>0 and having all but secured advancement). He later started in two [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification <U+2013> CONCACAF Third Round|semifinal]] matches after the U.S. had secured advancement to the final round<U+2014>a 2<U+2013>1 loss at [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] and a 2<U+2013>0 win over [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]]. When Howard was suspended for a match at [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] due to accumulated yellow cards, Guzan started and helped earn a critical 2<U+2013>2 draw. Guzan also started the USA's 3<U+2013>0 win over [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] in the [[2009 Confederations Cup]]. On May 11, 2010, Guzan was named to the U.S. national team's provisional 30-man World Cup roster.

Since then, Guzan has sat back as a second choice to keeper Tim Howard. While Howard was recovering from a back injury, Guzan started in two World Cup qualifier matches in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - CONCACAF Fourth Round|fourth round]] in March 2013. He did not allow a goal during either match, picking up a 1-0 win over [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] at [[Dick's Sporting Goods Park]] and an historic 0-0 draw against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at [[Estadio Azteca]].

